  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Teachers and pre-service teachers generally perceive GeoGebra favorably, recognizing its utility in enhancing student understanding, especially in geometry (Zakaria & Lee, 2012; Horzum & Ünlü, 2017; Mingirwa, 2016).",
    "GeoGebra can improve teachers' mathematical thinking and instructional strategies (Hall & Chamblee, 2013; Agyei & Benning, 2016).",
    "However, successful implementation requires proper training and systemic support (Hohenwarter & Lavicza, 2007; Mwingirwa & Marguerite, 2016).The third cluster, \"GeoGebra as a Learning Tool,\" investigates how GeoGebra can be employed to enhance students' mathematical knowledge, particularly in solving mathematical problems in domains such as calculus, functions, and calculations.",
    "Multiple studies have demonstrated GeoGebra's effectiveness in improving conceptual and procedural knowledge in calculus, geometry, algebra, and trigonometry (Zulnaidi & Zamri, 2017; Uwurukundo et al., 2020).",
    "GeoGebra aids in visualizing complex concepts, particularly in calculus, making learning more engaging and accessible (Arini & Dewi, 2019; Yerizon et al., 2021)."
  ],
